Temba Bavuma celebrates after scoring a century (100 runs) during the second one day international (ODI) cricket match between South Africa and England at Mangaung Oval in Bloemfontein on January 29, 2023. JOHANNESBURG - Temba Bavuma will be part of the inaugural SA20 league after having been snubbed at last year's player auction. The Proteas limited-overs captain has joined the Sunrisers Eastern Cape until the end of the season. Bavuma's eye-catching century in the second ODI against England showed off his limited overs skill.  It's taken a while, but Temba Bavuma will be part of the inaugural SA20 league, having been snubbed at last year's player auction. #DStv403 pic.twitter.com/5jjj4v7s3O